.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-WORKSPACE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.2.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-workspace \- Manage the expiring scratch workspace (hpc\-workspace ws_* tools)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose workspace [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Allocate, inspect, extend, or release the hpc\-workspace\-managed scratch workspace configured in settings, using the site's ws_find/ws_allocate/ws_extend/ws_release/ws_list tools. Runs the tools locally (on the login node or a dev machine); resolved facts are persisted per profile in .hpc\-compose/workspace\-state.toml.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBstatus\fR
Show the configured workspace's path and expiry. See hpc\-compose\-workspace\-status(1).
.TP
\fBallocate\fR
Allocate the configured workspace if it does not exist. See hpc\-compose\-workspace\-allocate(1).
.TP
\fBextend\fR
Extend the configured workspace's lifetime. See hpc\-compose\-workspace\-extend(1).
.TP
\fBrelease\fR
Release the configured workspace (destructive). See hpc\-compose\-workspace\-release(1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB-v\fR, \fB--verbose\fR
Increase diagnostic verbosity; repeat for debug\-level logs.
.TP
\fB--debug\fR
Enable debug\-level diagnostics (equivalent to \-vv unless RUST_LOG is set).
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--offline\fR
Forbid SSH, remote delegation, Slurm scheduler contact, submissions, allocations, and cancels.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose workspace status
hpc\-compose workspace allocate
hpc\-compose workspace extend \-\-days 30
hpc\-compose workspace release \-\-yes
.fi
